# Testing — Colyseus server

## Layout
- **Unit tests**: `colyseus-server/src/tests/*.test.ts`
- **Naming**: `*.test.ts` (Jest)
- **Runner**: Jest (configured in colyseus-server)

## Commands
```bash
cd colyseus-server
npm test                    # all tests
npm test -- --runInBand     # single-thread (avoid flakiness)
npm test -- src/tests/ai-mob-decision.test.ts   # one file
```

## Setup
- **Setup file**: `colyseus-server/src/tests/setup.ts` (mocks, globals)
- **No live server** required for unit tests (mocks for GameState, physics, etc.)

## Conventions
- Use `performance.now()` for gameplay timing in tests (align with 02-accuracy-correctness).
- Mock EventBus / room when testing handlers.
- One focused assertion per test where possible; group in `describe` by feature.

## Integration
- For full server tests: start server (`npm run dev` or `docker-compose up -d`) then run tests that connect to `ws://localhost:2567` if present.
- Most tests in `src/tests/` are unit tests with no server required.

